title: TV best bets: Sun., Oct., 11
text:
TV best bets: Sun., Oct., 11 October 11, 2015 Last updated: Sunday, October 11, 2015, 1:21 AM The Record Print 
7 p.m., ABC: America’s Funniest Home Videos — One of the longest-running shows currently on broadcast television, this program launches its 26th season with a very significant change — a new host. "Fresh Prince of Bel-Air" alum Alfonso Ribeiro takes over the duty of introducing amusing videos sent in by viewers, and the line of succession is appropriate — Ribeiro won season 19 of "Dancing With the Stars," still hosted by Tom Bergeron, who also presided over this series for 15 of its rounds. Buy this photo Mary Lynn Rajskub stars in "Brooklyn Nine-Nine" at 8:30 tonight on Fox. 
8:30 p.m., FOX: Brooklyn Nine-Nine — Boyle’s (Joe Lo Truglio) love life is getting a lot of attention in the comedy’s new season, and that continues with the new episode "Boyle’s Hunch," featuring guest star Mary Lynn Rajskub ("24") as the next woman who’s possibly in line for the police detective’s affection. Her character is an art-gallery owner, and Jake (Andy Samberg) tries to help make a match of the couple. 
9:30 p.m., CBS: The Good Wife — Fresh off his run on "Extant," Jeffrey Dean Morgan joins another CBS series as he’s introduced as investigator Jason Crouse in the new episode "Innocents." He’s sought by Alicia (Julianna Margulies) to help in a case involving vandalism at a museum. Howard Lyman’s (Jerry Adler) behavior becomes a problem again, with Cary (Matt Czuchry) trying to intervene. 
10:01 p.m., ABC: Quantico — Parental problems plague Alex (Priyanka Chopra) in both the past and present in the new episode "Cover." During her Quantico training, as she and her fellow trainees get an education in profiling, she discovers facts about her father ... but now, while she’s on the run, her mother (guest star Anna Khaja) appears on television and pleads that she turn herself in. 
10:01 p.m., TLC: 90 Day Fiancé — Six new couples use a unique visa that allows foreigners into the United States to live with their fiancés for the first time and decide whether to marry over the course of 90 days as this unscripted series returns for a third season with the new episode "Departures and Arrivals." Couples for this season include — Fernando, 39, of Miami, and Carolina, 22, from Colombia; Josh, 22, of Rexburg, Idaho, and Aleksandra, 21, from Russia; and Loren, 27, of New York and Alexei, 27, from Israel.
